    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent core, anchored by **Junior Caminero** (76.66), who claims our highest efficiency score of the day. A favorable wind blowing out at the stadium, paired with a solid matchup against Keller, makes **Junior Caminero** the priority play in the two-hole. Close behind are our speed-oriented assets at the top and bottom of the lineup; both **Trea Turner** (69.15) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (69.44) benefit from significant platoon advantages today. Despite the potential threat of a sub-2.00s pop-time from an elite opposing catcher, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** remains a high-floor start because of his aggressive dynamic platoon profile, which effectively mitigates the risk posed by his batting order slot.\n\nOur decision-making process was pushed to the limit by **Josh Smith** (40.62), who was the final omission from the starting nine. While **Josh Smith** offers a decent dynamic platoon boost against Woo, his overall efficiency score failed to clear the threshold required to displace the high-OBP production of **Carson Benge** (63.27) or the power-upside provided by **Yordan Alvarez** (67.90). Elsewhere, we remain cautious regarding **Dillon Dingler** (48.35); while he benefits from a strong platoon edge, the underlying SP skill of Crochet creates a significant drag on his ceiling. We will monitor the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Zac Veen** closely, as both remain sidelined, leaving us to rely on our active speed merchants like **Victor Scott II** to maintain our competitive edge in the SB category.",
